  • Enum Constant Details

    • TRIAZINE

      public static final H2SScavenger.ScavengerType TRIAZINE
      MEA-triazine based scavenger. Most common for oilfield applications. Reaction: 3H2S + C6H15N3O3 → products (dithiazine + thiadiazine). Typical stoichiometry: 3.5-6.0 lb scavenger per lb H2S.

    • GLYOXAL

      public static final H2SScavenger.ScavengerType GLYOXAL
      Glyoxal-based scavenger. Good for high CO2 systems. Typical stoichiometry: 4.0-7.0 lb scavenger per lb H2S.

    • IRON_SPONGE

      public static final H2SScavenger.ScavengerType IRON_SPONGE
      Iron sponge (iron oxide on wood chips). Used for dry gas treating. Regenerable with air. Capacity: 0.4-0.6 lb H2S per lb iron oxide.

    • CAUSTIC

      public static final H2SScavenger.ScavengerType CAUSTIC
      Caustic (NaOH) scrubbing. Very effective but produces liquid waste. Stoichiometry: 2.4 lb NaOH per lb H2S (based on 2NaOH + H2S → Na2S + 2H2O).

    • LIQUID_REDOX

      public static final H2SScavenger.ScavengerType LIQUID_REDOX
      Liquid redox processes (LO-CAT, SulFerox). Catalytic conversion to elemental sulfur. Very high efficiency for large scale.
